            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en" resp="#VM"> <!-- add cf. with Sikel inscriptions -->
                <p>Abecedarium of which only the first four letters remain. The alpha is of the type with a dot on the inside instead 
                    of a horizontal stroke, which is common in the Sicilian context on defixiones 
                    (see <ref target="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JNJBXZFP">Brugnone 1978</ref>; 
                    <ref target="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JCF4E489">Tribulato, Mignosa 2021</ref>, 315 on the 
                    question of alpha variants in archaic Sicilian contexts). The delta also presents a similar ductus, with a dot inside.
                    On other abecedaries found in Sicily on ceramics see Tribulato 2017 (and on this document in particular p. 119).</p>
            </div>
